  <description><![CDATA[<p>Located in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c}" title="Levi">Levi's</a> ski resort, the modern Break Sokos Hotel is ready to welcome you to it's comfortable rooms, quirky interiors and great facilities. This property is all about the location, rooms are split across three buildings (Suvi, Loimu and Kide) and sit side by side so regardless of which building you stay in, all the shops, bars and restaurants are on your doorstep. The ski school, hire shop and nearest lift are just a 3 minute walk away and the popular Coffee House is located in the reception.  </p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>The Sokos Hotel is conveniently situated in the centre of the charming resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c}" title="Levi">Levi,</a> making it the ideal base for your winter adventure. You have quick access to the ski slopes, the resort's cross-country ski trails, as well as the various restaurants, cafes and shops dotted around.</p>
<h2>A range of restaurants </h2>
<p>Fuel up for the day at the <span>Kiisa breakfast buffet, there is a range of sweet and savoury options served daily, as well as various hot options. For dinner, you can enjoy a meal at one of the newest restaurants in Levi which is apart of the Break Sokos Hotel- Grill it! which specialises in meats and vegetables being cooked over a charcoal grill. Alternatively you can sample some of the lovely restaurants in resort, serving traditional Lappish cuisine, pizza or fine dining dishes.  </span><span>If you fancy and coffee and cake, head to Coffee House for a sustainably produced latte or americano and a sweet treat. The Coffee House also serves a range of sandwiches and biscuits throughout the day.</span></p>
<h2>Modern and comfortable </h2>
<p>The Break Sokos Hotel offers comfortable accommodation in the centre of Levi. Set across three different buildings, each room is furnished in a modern style influenced by the seasons.  Motifs of animals and the nature of Lapland feature in the rooms, whether it be paintings, curtains or photographs. The rooms we offer can sleep up to four people, making this an excellent choice for a small family, couples and even single travellers. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
